Foundation.AI.Inference.BitNet  (BitNet.Interop, BitNet.Sample)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The BitNet inference module wraps Microsoft Research's BitNet llama.cpp fork:

    https://github.com/microsoft/BitNet

via P/Invoke. The native binaries are not redistributed in this source tree;
consumers must build or obtain them separately. The upstream project is
licensed under the MIT License.

bitnet.cpp itself is built on two upstream projects, which are acknowledged
here for chain-of-attribution completeness:

  - llama.cpp by Georgi Gerganov and contributors
        https://github.com/ggerganov/llama.cpp
        bitnet.cpp is a fork of the llama.cpp inference framework. MIT License.

  - T-MAC by Microsoft Research
        https://github.com/microsoft/T-MAC/
        bitnet.cpp's optimized kernels are built on top of the Lookup Table
        methodologies pioneered in T-MAC. MIT License.

